entry.content:
# Steps to reproduce the problem
1. add DIV to the page
2. add css to make "fullscreen overlay": 
div {
		position: fixed;
		font-size: 52px;
		inset: 0;
		background: green
	} 
3. add css to make unexpectedly previously added DIV not full-screen
div {
  justify-self: center;
  align-self: center;
}

# Problem Description
With an update from current version i've got an issue that if you have DIV stretched with a "position: fixed; top: 0; left:0; right:0; bottom: 0;", it is unexpected that in that case now "justify-self: center" or "align-self: center" makes it not a full-screen already, it ruined markup at 200 my websites because this update changed previously implemented behaviour of the following css rules =/

I came with a Version 122.0.6261.69 (Official Build) (arm64)

# Summary
Fixed-position "fullscreen overlay" DIV not full-screen with "justify-self: center" is unexpected.

# Additional Data
Category: JavaScript \
Chrome Channel: Stable \
Regression: Yes

